,Recommended,288220,21897615,"Posted: 17 March, 2016",all,trixareforEVERYONE,"A lot of people are kinda 'meh' about early access but honestly, I forgot it was early access sometimes because the only problems the game had were bits of dialogue in the game were missing its audio but it was only a couple of lines and it's not even that noticable. It also has a few bugs, like when I went to load a game, sometimes the game would crash but all I had to do was start the game up again and it would work just fine. Those are the only real problems that would prevent someone from playing the game. As for the game itself, I love being able to change Sian's (pronounced 'Shawn' not 'Seeane' like I originally thought) clothes though I hope the final game will have some more options for clothing and that some of the outfits will be a little cuter (I have a thing about ankle length skirts and this game has a few of them and it kind of bothers me but that's just nitpicking).The only other thing that bothered me was the stories in the routes because I mostly found them a little boring and hope that there might be a little more drama or background information to keep people hooked in the final game. But it is still A LOT of fun and since it's still in development, the final game looks like it'll be a lot of fun. Well, I've gone on sounding like a pretentious weirdo for long enough so all I can say is, if you like otome games, this one is a fun one to play and to also check out SakeVisual for other games they've made because they are pretty fun and a lot of them are free (though only a few of them are otome games)"
,Recommended,288220,16510823,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,AmayaTsuki,"I knew the game was an Early Access game, but assumed that, for the price, there'd be a bit more content.The artwork is beautiful and the music is pretty decent. All of the characters are really well written. I've played a lot of VN's and this is one of the few where I actually like all of the characters. The story is interesting and the main character is likeable. So, overall, I'd say this is a good game.There's a stat raising element that can get a little obnoxious after awhile. There's very little room for error and I had to restart A LOT  to get the good endings. I don't mind stat raising, but this one is a bit tough without a walkthrough.Like I said, for $30 you're not getting much right now. No voices. Only a few of the endings (as opposed to the 15 they say there are) and only a few of the characters are romanceable as of right now. I'd definitely recommend this game, but only after more content has been released. Until then, save your money."
76561198119640580,Recommended,288220,15942946,"Posted: 22 May, 2015",all,Rinka,"This game is fun, but it is not yet done. And I have never once gotten a perfect ending with any of the characters. I can get the romance skill all the way up but not the friendship skills, I even started saving before I answered in any of the dialog. Mind you I got this game probably 6 months ago. I don't think it is worth it's price, but then again it's not yet complete. I do think this game would  be more worth it around $18, even if the voices where all done."
,Recommended,288220,29511054,Posted: 26 January,all,Cobalt_Tea☆,"Backstage pass is an incredible Visual novel,by a very talented group. Having played loved,their other game RE: Alistair Years ago,i was very excited to try a new game from them,and it tripled my expectations~The art is great,it has impressive and captivating intro and ending animations,a host of lovable characters (honestly,there was not a single on i didn't like) with great voices,and a story and world i found myself interested in.The main character,Sian,has an interesting personality- and one that i could personally relate to rather well.This game DOES require a lot of stat raising,which i know isn't everyone's cup of tea,but to be honest the stat raising somehow felt easier and more comfortable then some other games i've played in the past,which was great~$30 might be a bit much,but with all the play time,quality art,story and high replayablity,i assure you it's worth it- at least in my eyes~if you love visual novels,and don't mind stat raising DEFINITELY give this one a try. i'm sure you won't regret it :)"
